  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bcb\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baf\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0baf \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b89\u0ba4\u0bb5 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1 - \u0bb9\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb7 \u0b9f\u0bbf \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbe \u0b8e\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "International Monetary Fund will not help Sri Lanka if talks fail - Harsha de Silva warns",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "Even if negotiations with the International Monetary Fund reach employee-level consensus, failure to negotiate with lenders could lead to serious crises.",
        "Dr. Harsha de Silva, Member of Parliament for the United People's Power, said the International Monetary Fund's hands were tied to help Sri Lanka.",
        "He made this statement at a press conference held at the office of the Leader of the Opposition in Colombo on Thursday.",
        "Pending completion of negotiations with the International Monetary Fund, it is essential to carry out short-term programs to meet the current needs of the country.",
        "The demand for the next 4 months is seen to be $ 4 billion. In addition, the International Monetary Fund, the World Bank, including bailout loans can not be without payment.",
        "It cannot borrow from abroad. Therefore, the friendly countries should seek help. It is essential that deep economic restructuring be undertaken in order to receive this assistance.",
        "The government must carry out in-depth reforms in its policies, including tax, expenditure, relief, public finance, public institutions, public service and pensions. Otherwise it is impossible to recover from these crises.",
        "We have approached the International Monetary Fund on 16 occasions before this. In those cases we engaged in negotiations only with the International Monetary Fund. But this time negotiations with third parties also have to be carried out.",
        "Those third parties are our lenders. Officials of two internationally recognized organizations have been invited to the country to negotiate with them regarding debt restructuring.",
        "They are currently engaged in reviewing data on the economy. There is a situation where even the data to be submitted to them cannot be fully obtained.",
        "This was revealed by the Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe in the last parliamentary session. The companies will start negotiations with the lenders only after the completion of these reviews.",
        "So even if staff level agreement is reached with the International Monetary Fund, if agreement is not reached in the negotiations with the lenders, it will face severe difficulties.",
        "Lenders' decision is based on the government's policies for deep economic reforms. Deep economic reforms cannot be undertaken by this government alone. Therefore, we are insisting that an all-party government should be formed.",
        "Every minute that Gotabhaya Rajapakse does not step down will only exacerbate the crisis facing the people. How can this government, which failed to build the country when it saw a two-thirds majority, do it now? It is not a demand that an all-party government be formed now. It has become an essential necessity. He called for the resignation of Gotabhaya Rajapaksa."
      ],
